BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (67): BTV-8, VECTOR FREE PERIOD
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Sun 30 Dec 2007
From: Sabine Zentis <CVLonghorns@aol.com>

[ProMED-mail's posting "Bluetongue - Europe (65): BTV-8, update, UK
20071222.4118" reported about UK Defra's declaration of a vector-free
period for bluetongue disease, in power from 20 Dec 2007.

The following Internet-derived information addresses the situation in
other BTV-8 affected countries. - Mod.AS]

1. Germany - no similar declaration could be found.

2. Luxembourg has declared the vector-free period, starting from 21
Dec 2007. Source:
<http://www.ma.public.lu/actualites/communiques/2007/12/20071220_01/index.html>

3. Belgium has declared the vector-free period starting from 13 Dec
2007. Source:
<http://www.favv-afsca.fgov.be/home/press/_documents/2007-12-20_blauwtong_nl.pdf>

4. Netherlands has declared the vector-free period starting from 12
Dec 2007 (compared to 18 Dec in 2006). Source:
<http://www.minlnv.nl/portal/page?_pageid=116,1640524&_dad=portal&_schema=PORTAL&p_node_id=439303>

--
